  mutate(datetime=paste(Date, Time)) %>%

Hourly sum and average

hours<-data%>%
  group_by(tube, stage)%>%
  summarize(sum=sum(act),
            mean=mean(act)
)
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'tube'. You can override using the
## `.groups` argument.
rem2<-hours %>% filter(sum>0)
rem<-as.data.frame(rem2$tube)
colnames(rem) <- "tube"
data2<-left_join(rem, data, by="tube")

hours2<-data2%>%
  group_by(hour, tube, stage)%>%
  summarize(sum=sum(act),
            mean=mean(act)
)
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'hour', 'tube'. You can override using the
## `.groups` argument.
hours3<-data2%>%
  group_by(hour)%>%
  summarize(sum=sum(act),
            mean=mean(act)
)

Hourly sum and average

hours<-data2%>%
  group_by(tube, stage)%>%
  summarize(sum=sum(act),
            mean=mean(act)
)
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'tube'. You can override using the
## `.groups` argument.
rem2<-hours %>% filter(sum>0)
rem<-as.data.frame(rem2$tube)
colnames(rem) <- "tube"
data2b<-left_join(rem, data2, by="tube")

hours2<-data2b%>%
  group_by(hour, tube, stage)%>%
  summarize(sum=sum(act),
            mean=mean(act)
)
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'hour', 'tube'. You can override using the
## `.groups` argument.
hours3<-data2b%>%
  group_by(hour)%>%
  summarize(sum=sum(act),
            mean=mean(act)
)

All data
